47:19.001 --> 47:23.101
Incidentally, Charlie Brown,
I want you to take this.

47:23.167 --> 47:27.101
My blanket.
My life. My all.

47:27.167 --> 47:29.101
It will bring you luck.

47:29.167 --> 47:31.533
Gee, Linus. That's very nice of you.

47:31.600 --> 47:32.600
Here.

47:32.667 --> 47:33.734
I don't think I...

47:33.800 --> 47:34.934
here.

47:36.067 --> 47:37.734
Well, ok.

47:38.700 --> 47:40.401
Thanks, Linus.
Here!

47:40.468 --> 47:41.600
So long, Linus.

47:41.667 --> 47:43.301
Here!

47:43.368 --> 47:46.867
Return victorious,
Charlie Brown!

47:46.934 --> 47:49.034
Or don't come back
at all.

47:49.101 --> 47:55.001
You can do it,
Charlie Brown!

47:55.067 --> 47:58.867
Return victorious,
Charlie Brown.

48:55.434 --> 48:58.533
Schroeder, do you think
Charlie Brown will win?

48:58.600 --> 49:01.800
Do you think that Charlie
Brown has a chance?

49:01.867 --> 49:04.001
Well, he's been
practicing a lot.

49:04.067 --> 49:06.201
I think
he has a good chance.

49:09.267 --> 49:13.368
The young man these days has
to practice a lot, doesn't he?

49:13.434 --> 49:16.633
A young man these days
has to work very hard

49:16.700 --> 49:19.600
to be able to support a wife, doesn't he?

49:19.667 --> 49:21.934
Who said anything
about a wife?

49:25.667 --> 49:28.800
Do piano players make a
lot of money, Schroeder?

49:29.468 --> 49:31.533
Some do.

49:31.600 --> 49:34.334
If they practice
very hard, I guess.

49:36.834 --> 49:39.434
Keep practicing, kiddo.

49:41.633 --> 49:43.201
Incidentally,
who is this?

49:43.267 --> 49:44.934
George washington?

53:47.101 --> 53:48.934
What's going on here?

53:51.734 --> 53:52.834
Well?

53:52.900 --> 53:54.734
I can't help it.

53:54.800 --> 53:58.401
I made the mistake of giving
my blanket to Charlie Brown

53:58.468 --> 54:01.633
to take to that spelling bee
for good luck.

54:01.700 --> 54:06.368
Now, I keep fainting.
I keep passing out.

54:06.434 --> 54:07.700
Why don't you
go outside

54:07.767 --> 54:09.700
and get a breath
of fresh air?

54:13.900 --> 54:15.001
Oh.

54:19.767 --> 54:23.533
Woe is me. I'm dying.
My race is run.

54:23.600 --> 54:27.468
Why did I let Charlie Brown
take my blanket?

54:27.533 --> 54:30.167
I've got to get
my blanket back.

54:36.301 --> 54:38.434
See, I'm always passing out.

54:39.967 --> 54:42.434
Snoopy, it's up to you to help me.

54:42.500 --> 54:45.101
I just gotta have
my blanket back.

54:45.167 --> 54:47.234
I gotta have my blanket.

54:48.468 --> 54:50.567
I don't know
what's happening to me.

54:50.633 --> 54:53.700
Maybe you can come with me
to find Charlie Brown

54:53.767 --> 54:55.967
and get my blanket back.

56:22.067 --> 56:23.368
Disgrace.

56:23.434 --> 56:27.600
D-i-s-g-r-a-c-e.

56:27.667 --> 56:29.101
Disgrace.

56:29.167 --> 56:32.500
In choosing between
"I-e" and "e-i"

56:32.567 --> 56:35.101
"e-i" is used
after the letter "c."

56:35.734 --> 56:37.267
This is too much.

56:37.334 --> 56:40.301
I'm so tired I can
hardly stay awake.

56:40.368 --> 56:43.267
Maybe I'd better go to bed.

56:43.334 --> 56:46.667
But if I give up now, the
kids will never forgive me.

56:47.500 --> 56:49.533
I can't keep up this pace.

56:50.934 --> 56:52.834
Maybe I should
just tell 'em all

56:52.900 --> 56:54.867
that my health
is more important.

56:59.067 --> 57:00.134
Yes, health.

57:00.201 --> 57:03.434
H-e-a-l-t-h. Health.

57:03.500 --> 57:07.368
I'm getting delirious.
I better get a hold on myself.

57:07.434 --> 57:09.434
I need something
in my stomach.

57:09.500 --> 57:12.468
Stomach. S-t-o-m-a-c-h.
Stomach.

57:12.533 --> 57:14.567
I'd better call room service.

57:14.633 --> 57:15.633
Service.

57:15.700 --> 57:17.934
S-e-r-v-i-c-e.
Service.

57:19.533 --> 57:22.434
Yes, service.
Yes, that's it.

57:22.500 --> 57:24.667
"I" before "e"
save after "d."

57:25.500 --> 57:27.201
Hello, yes, hello.

57:29.967 --> 57:31.667
Oh, did I ring?

57:31.734 --> 57:33.533
Yes, I guess I rang.

57:33.600 --> 57:35.667
Rang. R-a-n-g. Rang.

57:36.900 --> 57:37.900
What?

57:37.967 --> 57:40.234
Oh, yes, room service.

57:40.301 --> 57:42.533
I want room service. Ooh.

57:42.600 --> 57:46.034
Could you please send me a bowl
of dry cereal and a glass of milk?

57:46.101 --> 57:49.434
Listen, what was it?
"L" before "e" after milk?

57:55.167 --> 57:57.201
Thump. T-h-u-m-p. Thump.

58:03.800 --> 58:06.401
Hey.

58:28.900 --> 58:33.134
My blanket, Charlie Brown.
My blanket.

58:33.201 --> 58:36.633
I can't be without it.

58:36.700 --> 58:41.401
After I gave you my blanket,
my life has been a nightmare.

58:41.834 --> 58:42.934
Phew.

58:48.001 --> 58:50.934
See? I keep passing out.

58:51.001 --> 58:54.267
I can't be
without my blanket.

58:56.567 --> 58:59.734
I need my blanket,
Charlie Brown.

58:59.800 --> 59:02.834
Gee, Linus, I don't know
what's with your blanket.

59:04.301 --> 59:05.800
I've been so busy
studying

59:05.867 --> 59:07.834
that I forgot
all about your blanket.

59:07.900 --> 59:10.034
Forgot about
my blanket!

59:10.101 --> 59:11.101
Phew.

59:12.034 --> 59:15.700
Woe, woe, woe is me.

59:15.767 --> 59:17.533
Gee, I'm sorry, Linus.

59:17.600 --> 59:22.201
I really have been studying so
hard I must have misplaced it.

59:22.267 --> 59:24.967
Maybe I left it
in the lobby. Hmm.

59:26.767 --> 59:29.700
No, I think I left it
at the library.

59:29.767 --> 59:32.767
I really haven't gone any
place except for the library.

59:32.834 --> 59:35.234
That's it. I must have
left it at the library.

59:35.301 --> 59:38.900
Library!
I give him a good luck charm,

59:38.967 --> 59:41.034
my beautiful blanket,

59:41.101 --> 59:43.633
and he thinks
it's at the library.

59:44.734 --> 59:47.134
Charlie Brown,
I ought to kick you!

59:53.101 --> 59:55.700
Linus! Linus!
Speak to me.

59:55.767 --> 59:58.001
I'm sure the blanket
is at the library.

59:58.067 --> 59:59.500
Take old Snoopy
with you.

59:59.567 --> 01:00:01.267
He's a hunting dog.
He'll...

01:00:02.167 --> 01:00:03.600
good grief.

01:00:05.500 --> 01:00:08.234
Well, he'll be happy to
help you find your blanket.

01:00:08.301 --> 01:00:09.934
I have to stay
and study.

01:00:10.001 --> 01:00:13.734
Tomorrow's the spelling bee
and I just have to study.

01:00:13.800 --> 01:00:15.834
Look in the hotel
lobby first,

01:00:15.900 --> 01:00:18.867
then go down 2 blocks,
right, then straight.

01:00:18.934 --> 01:00:20.500
You can't miss it.

01:00:20.567 --> 01:00:23.500
It's either at the library
or somewhere along the way.

01:00:32.533 --> 01:00:34.134
It isn't here.

01:00:55.134 --> 01:00:56.700
It isn't here!

01:01:06.134 --> 01:01:07.700
It isn't here!

01:01:13.368 --> 01:01:17.500
Where is it? Where can it be?

01:05:11.034 --> 01:05:14.001
Where is it?
I don't see it.

01:05:14.934 --> 01:05:16.767
It isn't here.

01:05:19.834 --> 01:05:24.267
It's gone.
My poor blanket is gone.

01:05:25.001 --> 01:05:29.533
Woe is me. I'm sunk.

01:05:29.600 --> 01:05:34.401
That scoundrel, Charlie
Brown, lost my blanket.

01:05:45.001 --> 01:05:47.767
All right, you stupid beagle, snap to it!

01:05:47.834 --> 01:05:51.267
You've been no help at all
in finding my blanket.

01:05:55.334 --> 01:05:58.134
Some hunting dog!

01:05:58.201 --> 01:06:02.401
The world is ending and he
can't even help find a blanket.

01:06:05.034 --> 01:06:08.633
It's that blockhead
Charlie Brown's fault.

01:06:08.700 --> 01:06:11.334
If I hadn't
felt sorry for him,

01:06:11.401 --> 01:06:13.600
this would
never have happened.

01:06:13.667 --> 01:06:17.001
Never feel sorry
for blockheads!

01:06:17.067 --> 01:06:20.101
I'll never forgive
that Charlie Brown.

01:06:30.700 --> 01:06:32.700
Good morning, Linus
and Snoopy.

01:06:32.767 --> 01:06:36.800
Snoopy, S-n-o-o-p-y. Snoopy.

01:06:36.867 --> 01:06:39.334
Well, Charlie Brown,
you really did it.

01:06:41.067 --> 01:06:44.101
We looked for that blanket
all over the city.

01:06:46.067 --> 01:06:48.900
And as for this
hunting dog of yours,

01:06:48.967 --> 01:06:51.234
he's completely useless.

01:06:51.301 --> 01:06:56.234
Useless.
U-s-e-l-e-s-s. Useless.

01:06:58.101 --> 01:06:59.633
Gee, I'm sorry, Linus.

01:06:59.700 --> 01:07:01.201
I don't know what to say.

01:07:01.267 --> 01:07:02.967
S-a-y. Say.

01:07:04.134 --> 01:07:06.734
I've got to get ready
for the contest.

01:07:06.800 --> 01:07:12.301
Contest.
C-o-n-t-e-s-t. Contest.

01:07:12.368 --> 01:07:16.201
I'll never see
my blanket again.

01:07:18.201 --> 01:07:21.734
Washing.
W-a-s-h-i-n-g. Washing.

01:07:50.800 --> 01:07:52.167
Ugh!

01:09:03.267 --> 01:09:06.067
"I" before "e"
when followed by "c."

01:09:22.700 --> 01:09:24.834
Good luck, Charlie Brown.

01:09:37.167 --> 01:09:40.134
Hi. I'm a friend
of one of the contestants.

01:09:59.633 --> 01:10:02.468
I'm a friend of one
of the contestants.

01:10:24.468 --> 01:10:26.934
That blockhead
better deliver.

01:10:27.001 --> 01:10:31.001
I'm sure Charlie Brown
will perform commendably.

01:10:31.067 --> 01:10:33.101
It's gonna start.
Here it is.

01:10:33.167 --> 01:10:36.334
It's sydney or the bush
for Charlie Brown.

01:10:46.967 --> 01:10:52.468
When a word ends in "c," a "k"
is added before "e," "i," or "y."

01:10:52.533 --> 01:10:55.867
That blockhead.
He's falling asleep.

